hoe, made from the macerated remains of six mil\nlion dollar bills which were destroyed when the new currency was Issued,\nwas exhibited by the Bureau of Engraving post of the American Legion\n;it the Legion convention in Boston.\nlong hood lines sweep back to blend\ngracefully into the new Fisher bodies.\nAnd never was Fisher\u2019s fine crafts\nmanship more evident than in the\nbodies cf the new Chevrolet Six!\nNot only arc the bodies roomier and\nmore comfortable, but as you study\nthem you will discover many gratify\ning new features and refinements.\nMechanically, too, the new Chevrolet\nSix is a better automobile. The\nwheelbase is longer. The frame is\nstronger. The steering is easier. The\nclutch is more durable. There is a\nsmoother, quieter, easier shifting\ntransmission. In fact, wherever finer\nmaterials and more advanced design\ncould add to Chevrolet quality or\nincrease Chevrolet\u2019s traditional econ\nomy of ow nership\u2014improvement has\nbeen made. See the new Chevrolet Six\n\u2014for here is the Grea t American Valucl\nNOGALES INTERNATIONAL\nThanksgiving Day\n(Continued from Pasre 1)\nwho are heavily burdened.\nNOW THEREFORE, in recogni\ntion of many benefits conferred up\non us; in conformity with establish\ned custom and pursuant to the pro\nclamation of the President of the\nUnited States, the Honorable Her\nbert Hoover, I, John C. Phillips,\ngovernor of Arizona, hereby desig\nnate Thursday, November 27, 1930,\nas Thanksgiving day, and I most\nearnestly urge all citizens to invoke\nthe beneficence of a kindly deity;\nto commemorate with appropriate\nceremonies the example of our fore\nfathers which found sincere expres\nsion on the first Thanksgiving day\nin 1621, to the end that all shall\nbe ever mindful of the benevolence\nand lovihg care of our divine fath\ner.\u201d\n\ni Holbrook Whiting Brothers\nbuilding addition to garage.\nJerome \u2014Search being made on\nKing Brothers ranch property on\nUpper Verde, for radium bearing\nore.\n1931 CHEVROLET MODELS NOW\nON DISPLAY THRUOUT NATION\nChevrolet\u2019s new oar for 1931,\npriced substantially below current\nlevels, is now on display through\nout the nation.\nHeralded as \u201cThe Great Ameri\ncan Value\u201d, the new car boasts a\ntwo-inch increase in wheelbase,\nlarger and roomier bodies by Fisher\nwith mohair or broadcloth as op\ntional trimming, and scores of re\nfinements in appearance and per\nformance despite the new prices\nwhich bring the level for the 1931\ncar to a far lower figure than any\nChevrolet, four or six, has ever sold.\nDealers throughout the United\nStates have put the new models on\nexhibition nearly two months in\nadvance of the customary date for\nthe showing of the annual new car.\nThis move in advancing the an\nnouncement date, it was felt by\nChevrolet officials, would render a\ndistinct contribution to the cause\nof general business revival by in\nsuring extraordinary activity during\ntwo normally dull business months\nfor the 200,000 people throughout\nUnited States who depend directly\nupon Chevrolet for their livelihood.\nThe nineteen domestic production\nplants of the Chevrolet organization\nare now in full swing on the new\nmodel, according to W. S. Knudsen,\npresident, and shipments are going\nout to dealers to assure immediate\ndelivery of all models.\nFundamentally the new model\nembodies the same basic features\nwhich, since the introduction of the\nChevrolet Six, enabled it to achieve\na popularity exceeding Chevrolet\u2019s\nformer four cylinder model and four\ntimes as great as any other six cyl\ninder car. However, scores of im\nprovements and refinements have\nbeen made this year\u2014every change\ndesigned to increase the smartness,\nperformance, safety or durability of\nthis latest General Motors model.\nAmong the improvements are a\nfully insulated front compartment,\neasier steering, more durable clutch,\nsmoother and quieter transmission,\nand liberal use of rustless chromium\nplate on exposed bright parts. Four\nLovejoy hydraulic shock absorbers,\nand fully enclosed, weatherproof\nfour-wheel brakes continue as stan\nWHEN YOU BUY YOUR NEW CAR\nInsist That The Dealer Equip It With\nTIRES\nThere is no substitute for this fine tire, altho some\ntires sell at a higher price.\nWhen it comes to economy, freedom from tire trouble,\nand satisfaction on the road, the Double Eagle is\ntruly \u201cThe Tire of Tires\u201d. Built by Goodyear with\nout regard to cost and with the knowledge that it is\ntoo good a tire for the majority of people to buy, yet\nthe sales far exceeded the anticipated demand.\nCheshire Bros. Motor Co.\nNOGALES, ARIZ., TUESDAY, NOV., 18, 1930\ndard equipment.\nIn the line of nine body types are\nthree open models\u2014the roadster,\nphaeton and sport roadster, and six\nclosed models\u2014the coach, sedan,\nspecial sedan, the three-window\ncoupe, the five-window coupe, and\nthe sport coupe. All models have\nsmart new wire wheels, with 4.75\nby 19 tires, as standard equipment.\nThe two-inch increase in wheel\nbase has been utilized throughout\nthe line to increase the roominess\nand comfort of the new bodies.\nSmart new Duco color combinations,\nthe addition of decorative body fea\ntures and a head-on appearance ex\ntensively changed from the 1930 car\ncombine to make the 1931 model\ndecldely finer in appearance than\nany of its predecessors.\nThe radiator has a larger cooling\ncapacity this year, and is improved\nin both efficiency and appearance.\nA new treatment of the shell makes\nit appear much higher and the sides\nappear to have more curvature.\nFront fenders have been raised\nslightly at the forward end to ach\nieve a lighter and finer appearance,\nand the sweep of the rear fenders\nhas been made more pronounced.\nThe hood in longer, with a higher\ncrown in the upper panels.\nThe new Fisher bodies all have a\nraised belt line to emphasize the low\nappearance of the car achieved by\nthe deeper side body panels, with\ntheir slight outward bulge.\nAn outstanding feature of the new\nbodies is the better vision made pos\nsible from the driver\u2019s seat by\nslightly lowering the seat and rais\ning the header bar which runs a\ncross the top of the windshield.\nAn improved rear end appearance\nis achieved by a newly designed\npanel concealing the rear cross\nmember and the gas tank. The black\nenameled panel is set off by a large\nchrome plated filler cap on the tank.\nThe interiors of all bodies have 1\nbeen redesigned to take full advan-'\ntage of the extra roominess provided\nby the two-inch increase in wheel\n\nbase. The result is a \u201cbig car\u201d cf-,\nfeet in the interior, just as the add\ned sweep to the exterior body lines\ncreates the impression of a consid-'\nerably larger car than last year. I\nSuch fine car features as assist\ncords, ash receivers, arm rests and\n(Turn To Page Five)\nSi HEAR IT\nTEST IT\nthe amazing new\no/HqfeMc\nPERFECTED\nSCREEN GRID\nSUPERHETERODYNE\ncomplete tvith tubes\nfree Trial\nEASIEST PAYMENTS\nGUARANTEED SERVICE\n\nG. A. Larriva\nDEALER\nLocated at American Drug\nStore Morley Ave.\nPhone 18","height":"25233","width":"18279"}}
